  "body": "The Crowdsale contracts use uint256 for timestamps, but the TokenTimelock contract uses an uint64.\r\n\r\nI expect using an uint64 consistently everywhere would be better, since the expected end of the universe would've passed 22 times the estimated current age of the universe before overflowing.\r\n\r\n(An added advantage would of course be smaller contract size, i.e. lower gas costs).",
