    "body": "Thanks fo reporting @Qqwy! The problem is actually in `TokenTimelock`. We should be using `uint256` everywhere.\r\n\r\n`uint256` is the only integer size native to the EVM. For all other integer sizes, the Solidity compiler generates extra operations to e.g. truncate on overflow. Because of this, using uint64 doesn't really lead to smaller contracts or less gas costs.",
